                            <comment id="13995922" author="misty" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 01:27:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the primary value-proposition for reverse scan might belong here, as &quot;One time when you don&apos;t need to use secondary indexes anymore&quot;: &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#secondary.indexes&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#secondary.indexes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;6.11.1.3 here is also a good place to have a note about the new functionality: &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#schema.casestudies&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#schema.casestudies&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe something here too: &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#reverse.timestamp&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#reverse.timestamp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or maybe I need a whole more abstract session about scanners.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995924" author="misty" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 01:30:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue documents the linked issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995929" author="misty" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 01:44:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added the following note in the first two places above:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;note&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;title&amp;gt;Reverse Scan API&amp;lt;/title&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;para&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;ulink url=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4811&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4811&quot; title=&quot;Support reverse Scan&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4811&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4811&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;/ulink&amp;gt; implements an API to scan a table or a range within a table in reverse, reducing the need to optimize your schema for forward or reverse scanning. This feature is available in HBase 0.98 and later. See &amp;lt;ulink url=&quot;https://hbase.apache.org/apidocs/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/client/Scan.html#setReversed%28boolean&quot; /&amp;gt; for more information.&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/para&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/note&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995937" author="misty" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 01:48:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if I actually need more than this. Ideally, the Scan API would have a working example. I can&apos;t figure out where in the Ref Guide would be the appropriate place for a working example of reverse scanning, since there doesn&apos;t even seem to be a working example of scanning.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995947" author="misty" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 02:04:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed how I generated the patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995948" author="misty" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 02:06:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch attached, which adds some notes to the chapter about schema design pointing out the new reverse scan API&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
